---
title: "Validation Pipeline with Advisory Polish Pass"
---
%% ABOUTME: Validation pipeline showing that blocking and advisory checks always run together; advisory findings are included in failure reports and in the polish pass
flowchart TD
    IN["Instrumented output"]
    G["Structural gate checks (all blocking)\nSyntax · Elision · Lint · Weaver static check"]
    B["Blocking quality checks\nSchema fidelity · Coverage · Code quality\nAPI-only · LLM judge (if new names)"]
    A["Advisory quality checks\n(always run, findings always collected)"]
    GFAIL(["Structural fail — file rejected"])
    DEC{"Any blocking\nfailures?"}
    SFAIL(["Fail — all findings returned\nblocking failures + advisory"])
    AGENT["Agent: one improvement pass\n(advisory findings only)"]
    RECHECK["Blocking validation re-runs"]
    IMPROVED(["Improved version committed"])
    PRIOR(["Prior passing version committed"])

    IN --> G
    G -->|all pass| B
    G -->|all pass| A
    G -->|any fail| GFAIL
    B --> DEC
    A --> DEC
    DEC -->|yes| SFAIL
    DEC -->|no| AGENT
    AGENT --> RECHECK
    RECHECK -->|pass| IMPROVED
    RECHECK -->|fail| PRIOR
